<HEAD>Two Homemade Bombs Discovered In Subway Stations</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Authorities defused two homemade bombs, one with a timing device, found in <LOCATION> Moscow </LOCATION> subway stations, a <ORGANIZATION> Foreign </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ministry </ORGANIZATION> spokesman said Friday. <PERSON> Gennady </PERSON> <PERSON> I. </PERSON> <PERSON> Gerasimov </PERSON> said the first device was spotted by passengers in a subway car at the <LOCATION> Paveletskaya </LOCATION> station. `` The bag seemed to belong to no one and contained a plastic bag wrapped in a newspaper,'' he said. <ORGANIZATION> KGB </ORGANIZATION> officers and subway security personnel found a pipe bomb inside the bag, <PERSON> Gerasimov </PERSON> said. The device was attached to an electric alarm clock and wired with batteries, he said. A similar device, without a clock, was discovered about an hour later at the Vdnkh metro station, the spokesman said. `` Both episodes appear to be linked,'' <PERSON> Gerasimov </PERSON> said. `` The <ORGANIZATION> KGB </ORGANIZATION> has begun an investigation.''
