<HEAD>Six Soldiers Die As Land-Rover Plunges Into River</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VALLADOLID, Spain (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Six soldiers died Saturday when the stolen vehicle they were in swerved off a road and plunged into a river, police said. The accident took place before dawn in the town of <LOCATION> Puente </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Duero </LOCATION>, a few miles outside the north-central city of <LOCATION> Valladolid </LOCATION>. The driver apparently lost control of the Land-Rover as he approached a bridge, police said. The victims, between the ages of 18 and 21, had been completing obligatory military service at the army's center for artillery ammunition and maintenance in <LOCATION> Valladolid </LOCATION>, a center spokesman said. <LOCATION> Valladolid </LOCATION> municipal police said the Land-Rover had been reported stolen Friday.
