<FIRST>r i AM-Greece-Strike     04-22 0158</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Greece-Strike,0162</SECOND>
<HEAD>Greek Airline Grounded By Strike</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATHENS, Greece (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Olympic Airways' flight and ground attendants defied a court order and grounded the national carrier Saturday with a 24-hour strike. A spokesman for the airline said all flights were canceled and that normal schedules would be resumed Sunday. Olympic's pilots and flight engineers did not join the walkout but were unable to fly without attendants, said the spokesman, who requested anonymity. The attendants are seeking overtime and additional pay for night flights. The strikers ignored a court order obtained by the airline Friday that forbade the walkout and threatened to fine and possibly jail participants. If the strikers' demands are not met, the airline spokesman said, the union has threatened to start a five-day walkout Monday. This week is Easter holy week for Greek Orthodox Christians, who celebrate Easter Sunday on April 30, and many if not all the airline's flights have long been sold out.
</TEXT>
